description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for admin assistant&#39;s to join us for an initial period of 3 months to provide support to our ward staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate will have excellent communication skills and a friendly manner as you will be communicating with a wide variety of people. You will be hard working, highly motivated and have the ability to work on your own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your duties may include, reception service for the ward, dealing with telephone enquiries, inputting and updating data on the hospital database, dealing with the general public as well as general administration duties such as filing, copying and ordering consumables. You will support the ward sister in her role completing more specific administrative tasks as requested.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should possess good IT and clerical skills. You will be dealing with the general public so it is paramount that you have good people skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at either Colchester or Ipswich Hospital various hours are available including weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally successful candidates will be able to commence without delay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that we may close this role early should we receive sufficient applicants&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal discussion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michelle Keable, Senior Recruitment Partner - michelle.keable@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
